<p>These projects use the <a href="/ibva-supercollider-interface/">OpenBCI-SuperCollider Interface</a> to read EEG data while listening to</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://nimetu.bandcamp.com/album/monolit">MONOLIT</a> by <a href="https://nimetu.org/"><kbd>Andrej Hrvatin</kbd></a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>binaural beats designed by Robert Monroe including <a href="https://www.thegatewayexperience.com/wave-i-discovery-3-cd-set/">The Gateway Experience</a> and</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>my own (live or prerecorded) frame drumming while shamanic journeying (meditating).</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>After recording sessions, internal visual imageries (visions) are interpreted in drawings. EEG data is currently analysed in SuperCollider only, but is planned to be analysed in Matlab as well.</p>

<p>To clarify, in contrast to several other projects in this research, the above projects do not use neurofeedback, they only record EEG activity affected by music for later (offline) analysis.</p>

